answers.body_markdown:
The immediate reason you receive the status logger error is that you remove you appender from the &quot;myPackage&quot; logger config, but you don&#39;t remove it from the root logger config.

If you want to remove an appender from **all** the logger configurations and stop it, run:
```lang-java
// Removes from all logger configuration and stops the appender
configuration.removeAppender(appenderName);
// Now we can also remove the logger configuration
configuration.removeLogger(packageName);
```

If you want to remove the appender from **just** one specific logger configuration you need to:
 1. Remove the appender from the logger configuration (`LoggerConfig#removeAppender`),
 1. Iterate over `Configuration#getLoggers` to see if no other logger config uses it,
 1. Stop the appender if it is no longer being used.

